This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with image super-resolution using deep learning methods. The paper also discusses the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and image transform domain, which are common topics in the Computer Vision field. 

The paper also involves regularization techniques, which are commonly used in Machine Learning (cs.LG) to prevent overfitting and improve generalization. 

The use of Discrete Cosine Transform (DCT) and pairwise orthogonality constraints suggest that the paper may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Information Theory (cs.IT) categories, respectively. 

Finally, the paper proposes a novel network structure for learning the SR mapping function, which involves optimizing the CDCT layer. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category, which deals with the optimization of neural networks.
